[normal]he impression to the public that they are genuinely conc
[normal]erned about a failing
[normal] institution, than it is to challenge the blatant injustices that have been brought to their at
[normal]tention over the past ten years. If the select committee had been in any way determi
[normal]ned to ensure a proper 
[normal]independent 
[normal]External Evaluation was carried out, it would not have 
[normal]allowed 
